i## Configuring Authentication		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iAfter installing the plugin, first add an `ldap_server` configuration		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iblock in the http section of nginx.conf. To prevent a single point of		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ifailure from taking down the entire authentication service, I		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
itemporarily used JumpCloud's LDAP service with the following		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iconfiguration:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  ldap_server jumpcloud {		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      url ldap://ldap.jumpcloud.com/ou=Users,o=[Your JumpCloud LDAP ID],dc=jumpcloud,dc=com?uid?sub?(objectClass=posixAccount);		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      binddn "uid=[LDAP Auth Username],ou=Users,o=[Your JumpCloud LDAP ID],dc=jumpcloud,dc=com";		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      binddn_passwd "[LDAP Auth Password]";		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      group_attribute "memberOf";		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      group_attribute_is_dn on;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      max_down_retries 3;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      connections 1;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      referral off;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      require valid_user;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      satisfy any;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  }		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThen add the following content to the server block or location block		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iyou want to protect:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  location /private {		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      auth_ldap "Forbidden";		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      auth_ldap_servers jumpcloud;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  }		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThis enables authentication using the specified LDAP server.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iNote: The LDAP authentication plugin conflicts with the http_addition		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iplugin. The specific symptom is that when both `auth_ldap` and `add_after_body`		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iare enabled in the same location, after successful username/password		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iauthentication, nginx fails to send webpage data, causing the browser		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ito spin until timeout. The temporary solution is to disable `add_after_body` :		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  # LDAP auth doesn't work well with http_addition, disable it		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  add_after_body "";		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
